# =============================================================================
# Vercel (Production)
# =============================================================================
# Add variables in: Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# Use Production (and Preview if needed), then redeploy so the bundle is rebuilt.
#
# This repo uses Create React App (react-scripts). Only REACT_APP_* names are inlined into
# the browser bundle. NEXT_PUBLIC_STEAM_API_KEY is read first in code for Next/Vite parity;
# for Vercel + this app, set at least one REACT_APP_* name below.
# =============================================================================

# --- Steam Web API (enables the Steam catalog path in the app) ---
# https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey
#
# Prefer for CRA / Vercel (inlined into client):
REACT_APP_STEAM_WEB_API_KEY=your_steam_web_api_key_here
# Optional shorter alias (same value; first non-empty wins after NEXT_PUBLIC):
# REACT_APP_STEAM_API_KEY=your_steam_web_api_key_here
#
# Next.js / Vite–style public name (checked first; not inlined by react-scripts unless you customize webpack):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STEAM_API_KEY=your_steam_web_api_key_here
#
# Store proxy (avoids CORS) — same host rewrite as vercel.json / setupProxy.js:
# REACT_APP_STEAM_STORE_PROXY=/api/steam-store
